<@U0EL0GLEL> <@U5DP0DTUZ> <@U243UT96G> talked to <@U02F8LF2X> just now about plans for our internal cubby setup 2.0 - we’re aiming for a quick setup using a few rolling carts in iron, the new NUCs google just sent us and what we have from our previous setup in the old building. hoping we can get that done by end of week or early next week (with respect to y’alls schedules of course).

in the meantime i’ll keep talking google folks and design about what we would want for a more permanent version here at 811, and i’ll welcome any input you might have as well for how we can make this something that is easy to work with and meets our needs from a dev standpoint (i.e. testing and maintenance)
do you guys need help w/ that?
i think any help offered is appreciated if you want to get experience with the setup process
but i’d also leave that up to <@U0EL0GLEL> and <@U02F8LF2X> to direct since i have no experience myself with that
ok, i’ll talk to them.  thanks
ok started gathering supplies. does anyone know where the planar rackmount power supply got tucked away?
its in canvas, under the desk on the left where the monitors are stacked
Thanks will conscript Matthew tomorrow and set up
